simcrs
------------------------------------------
SimCRS aims at providing a clean API and a simple implementation, as a C++
library, of a Travel-oriented Distribution System. It corresponds to the
simulated version of the real-world Computerized Reservation Systems (CRS).

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.4.12-3
  cygwin-3.1.5-1
  libairinv1.00-1.00.4-1bl1
  libairtsp1.01-1.01.7-1bl1
  libboost_program_options1.66-1.66.0-1
  libgcc1-9.3.0-2
  libsimcrs-devel-1.01.5-1bl1
  libsimcrs1.01-1.01.5-1bl1
  libsimfqt1.00-1.00.4-1bl1
  libstdair1.00-1.00.10-1bl1
  libstdc++6-9.3.0-2
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-9.3.0-2
  ninja-1.10.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/airsim/simcrs

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/airsim/simcrs/archive/simcrs-1.01.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack simcrs-1.01.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./simcrs-1.01.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/simcrs-1.01.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/simcrs-1.01.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsimcrs1.01-1.01.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsimcrs-devel-1.01.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(simcrs)
  /usr/bin/simcrs.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/simcrs.README
  /usr/share/doc/simcrs/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/simcrs/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/simcrs/ChangeLog
